India 102-2 at Lunch on Day 3 of First Cricket Test With England

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-23T12:24:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-23/india-102-2-at-lunch-on-day-3-of-first-cricket-test-with-england.html
India is 102-2 at lunch on day three
of the opening cricket Test against  England  at Lord’s in London.  Rahul Dravid is 15 not out and Sachin Tendulkar, seekng to
become the first player with 100 centuries in international
cricket, has 10 in India’s reply to England’s first innings 474-
8 declared.  Stuart Broad  took both wickets this morning.  The match is the 2,000th in the 134 years of elite Test
cricket. England can overtake India as the top team in the
International Cricket Council rankings if it wins the four-match
series by two Tests or more.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  